## More matches and better matches are not the same objective

If your metric is **raw match count**, the system can often improve it by being less selective, because more right-swipes mechanically create more possibilities for mutual likes. But a modern dating app does not only care about raw matches. BumbleŌĆÖs own hiring documents repeatedly tie recommendations to **match quality**, **meaningful outcomes**, **retention**, **engagement**, and **user trust**, and its 2026 investor materials highlight **mutual conversations** as an important success metric. Academic work on reciprocal recommendation reaches the same conclusion from a different angle: when you optimize crude match totals in a congested two-sided market, you can degrade the quality of outcomes. ŅłĆciteŅłéturn15view0Ņłéturn13view0Ņłéturn34search0Ņłéturn20view0Ņłéturn23view2Ņłü

